<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-09-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-09-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="1781" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1781">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 419.11D29/105.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Price</persName> to
                                    the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Panama</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-09-21">
                                        <hi rend="italic">September 21, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Panama has agreed to submit to arbitration only the claims growing
                                out of riot July 4, 1912. Claims incidental to subsequent riots have
                                not yet been presented. I should be glad to know as soon as
                                arbitration is decided upon.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Price.</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>